GitHub installation Manual

1.	Download & install Git from www.git-scm.com/downloads
2.	Go to git hub account & copy the repository link to clone it on local machine.
3.	Create a folder in local where you will keep all the repositories from git
4.	After Git is installed, open Git bash on local machine and configure your git hub account. E.g.
		git config --global user.name "Roopesh-g"
		git config --global user.email gujarathi.roopesh@gmail.com
5. 	Clone the Git hub repository using tye below command
		git clone <URL> (copied in step 2). First time it will ask for credentials
		
	